<!-- Button trigger modal -->
<button type="button" class="btn btn-light mr-1 px-2 py-1" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#transitionLettersModal">
<i class="bi bi-question-circle"></i>
</button>

<!-- Modal -->
<div class="modal" id="transitionLettersModal" tabindex="-1">
  <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h1 class="modal-title fs-5">Area transitions marked as letters on map</h1>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <p>If enabled, each area transition is marked on the map using the first letter of the neighboring area name.
        If disabled, transitions are marked using arrows.</p>
        <p>This option may be useful for players who are color-blind or who find the area colors unintuitive.
        <p>In both cases, transitions markers (letters or arrows) are colored according to the neighboring area's color.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
